On The Radio LyricsHey y'all, the Crash is rockin' on your radio

Sounds so good your hands will start clapping
And when we're finished rocking at the show
We'll be rocking on the radio
We go by the name of the mighty Crash
And we got a melody that's a sure enough smash
This here is going down with a great big splash
We're pulling all the tricks from out the stash
Reggie Reg, B-Stro, G-Man, ShuBee and
A brother by the name of EK Mike C
And don't you ever in your mind forget the Fantasy
Plus it's a whole of a lot of DJ Darryl C

We're rocking you down with a musical wave
While the rhythm makes you all become beat slaves
It makes you follow in tow to the musical flow
As we begin to rock you on the radio
Now that we've got your attention
There's something that we should mention
There's something that you all should know

Reggie Reg is rocking on the radio:
Now I received a phone call from a reliable source
But he was talking too fast and I got lost
I asked him to explain what he was talking about
My man was too excited, he began to shout
I finally figured what home boy was saying
"You'll never guess what the radio was playing"
I turned my stereo on and what do you know
Reggie Reg was rocking on your radio
You might also likeB-Stro is rocking on the radio:
I have powers that are only mine
I can make a blind man walk a straight line
I've dated queens, I beat up kings
I have 20 gold chains and 5 gold rings
I stole the throne, I wore the crown
I can even bench press 300 pounds
His name is B-Stro and you can call him a pro
Because I'll be rocking on the radio

Mike C is rocking on the radio:
The well balance of my talents is a gift from God
The fine sense of thought, it shouldn't be made hard
I'm a man that's strong, that's where I belong
You're guaranteed to get dissed if you tell me I'm wrong
Your mind is crunched as I take you to lunch
With my high powered rhymes I knock you out like a punch
No time to explain because it really don't matter
I'm EK Mike C and I will serve you on a platter

G-Man is rocking on the radio:
G-Man, but other rappers can address me as lord
The rhyme is my armor the mic is my sword
In an emcee joust I've never been bested, because
The rap I'm popping goes uncontested
Like a lethal weapon the rap will maim
Set your butt on fire with the heat from the flames
So don't you get out of line
You better stay in your place, because
If you don't I'm gonna diss your face
ShuBee is rocking on the radio:
Well I'm MC ShuBee, the emcee supreme
Be rocking on the mic with the gangsta lean
Been rocking the party since I was 17
Said I walk around town in designer jeans
And I should know that's stated as a fact, and
I'm the only emcee that got it like that
Well I'm MC ShuBee and I want you all to know
He's telling his story on the radio1Embed

We Are Known As Emcees (We Turn Party’s Out) Lyrics[Hook]
This is the way, this is the way
This is the way we harmonize
This is the way we harmonize
This is the way we harmonize, Uh-huh!

We are known as emcees
We always aim to please
5 bad brothers looking out for one another
We turn parties out
We turn parties out
We turn parties out
[Reggie Reg]
Now you heard us before so hear us again
The crew that was voted most likely to win
Cause Darryl C. rocks without a back spin
And our rhymes are so fly they blow on the wind
So come along on a musical trip
Keep in step, be sure you don't slip
Rock to the left and move to the right
And listen to the words we say on the mic

[Barry B-Stro]
I'm talented, well rounded
You see I have a lot of skills that I've hid
And when it's time to reveal
It's gonna be a big deal
All those skills plus sex appeal
My name is B-Stro and I like to chat
Because I hit 500 when I swing a bat
Big poster boy type athlete
There's not a challenge in the world that I can't beat

[EK Mike C]
I'm gonna stick to entertaining cause
It's something that I'm gaming
New faces many places big bucks for maiming [?]
I love a big crowd ever since I was a child
Hip hopping non stop is what made me go wild
What I bring to my people must be a treat
Day after day week after week
Something soft and sweet it's not nothing to eat
M-E, EK Mike C
You might also like[G-Man]
Now girls scream, melt like ice cream
When they see G-Man, the man of their dreams
Handsome face and physique to go with it
One look at me and they're ready to submit it
The G. is rough and I got the stuff
And it's up to the ladies to call my bluff
In the game of love I'm like a home run hitter
When it comes to getting women I'm a real go getter

[La ShuBee]
Well I'm MC ShuBee, the prince of sound
Because when I'm on the mic I make you get down
I'm too hot to trot too cold to freeze
There ain't no girl that I can't please
And when I get on the mic and start to rap
I'm guaranteed to put the ladies right in my trap
Tell your jealous boyfriends stay a mile on back
I'll put a rope 'round your neck and I won't cut you no slack
(Cut you no slack)

[Hook]
If you want to party and rock with everybody
So if you want to get down
With the 5 bad brothers, looking out for one another
We'll never steer you wrong
So if you want to hum sing along
We got a brand new funky song
We're gonna rock you all, all night long
You got to keep moving, just can't stop
Cause time is ticking much too fast
We will find another day of the music [?]
That we'll bring to you with class

[Hook]
This is the way we harmonize
This is the way we harmonize
This is the way we harmonize
Uh-huh, uh-huh

It's Darryl C. and the Crash Crew
So get yourself on the floor if you want some more
We're giving you more than what you bargained for
It's like a lime to a lemon, a lemon to a lime
Darryl C. if you're ready cut the record on time

We are known as emcees
We always aim to please
5 bad brothers looking out for one another
We turn parties out, we turn parties out1Embed

songs.lyrics:
MC Wars LyricsName, Emcees
Definition, masters of ceremony
One who specializes in the stimulation and
Manipulation of capacity crowds
Next is War
A state of open and
Declared armed hostile conflict
Between states, nations and emcees
What you are about to witness is
The total annihilation of
The current emcee population
This is war!
[Hook]
All you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing
War, you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing

[Reggie Reg]
Disco groups say this is to you
Ain't nothing but a threat from the Crash Crew
An act of aggression in your direction
Rocking the house to the best of perfection
And anyone who thinks they're the best
Step over this line and be put to rest
And they say without a doubt
That we can rock anyone and turn the party out
So all you emcees come out to play, cause
Reggie Reg has a rap that will ruin your day
Mike C, put your war gear on
Get on the mic and rock this song

[EK Mike C]
I've got style with fury creative and frightening
Take a bite of this if you want to start biting
I don't mind if you copy what I say, because
That's the main reason why I'm here today
It was the father of the lord who put me in command
He told me if I failed he would lend me a hand
But I'm a troop of God and I'm on a mission
To place emcees in the right position
I'm like a boulder on a mountain
Rolling down on a hill
Crash through buildings that's made of steel
Just look on the stage, it's the man drill
G-Man, secretary of war
Get on the mic and settle the score
You might also like[G-Man]
At first I didn't even want to waste my time
You've been nickled and dimed with cheap two cent rhymes
Counterfeit bit styles have been biting on mine
Remember when you called me a sucker emcee
I don't forget a thing, no sirree Bob
You big slob, you're working my job, and
I'll eat you up like corn on the cob
I reiterate, I won't hesitate
With my deejay scratching those two steel plates
I repeat, I won't retreat
Now clap your hands and stomp your feet
B-Stro, you throw the hardest blow
So get on the mic and rock the show

[Barry B-Stro]
An apocalypse of all emcees
We'll exterminate them like the worst disease
We have them in out grip we won't let them slip
We gonna choke no joke get them off of my tip
Like parasites just bugs in the night
They remind me of mosquito bites
With a swift kick they're not hard to fix
Darryl C and B-Stro eating sold out ticks
It's like Waterloo when you battle the crew
We're six bad brothers, not Scooby Doo
ShuBee, what you got to say
About the stupid emcees in the world today
[La ShuBee]
Everyone seems to have something to prove
About who rocks the house, who rocks the best moves
Everyone's fresh far as I can see, but
I'm the best emcee that could ever be
I rock the house I get the job done
I rock the party for you to have fun
I rock the mic from sun to sun
Because everybody knows Shu is number one

[Hook]
All you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing
War, you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing

Yes y'all this is the MC War
The mighty Crash is gonna settle the score
We're coming rough and hard so that you can't ignore
Gonna crash and crush and stomp you on the floor
Until the guys you root for start acting all silly
So we're gonna hit you hard with the heavy artillery
Combat ready the rap is steady
The rhymes are razor sharp it's a rap machete
So you shouldn't have tried to pass yourself off as friends
You shouldn't have said you were the king of rock
You're even trying to say you were the leader of the pack
Then you even said that you could never be wack
Now the Crash is here spinning a rap spell
We're about to raise a whole lot of hell
Raising Cain or Sam don't need a mic in our hands
So step to the left, get off my man
This is a promise not a threat by all means
This is record to the rappers from Brooklyn and Queens
The rhyme regiment doesn't need consent
The content intends to be belligerent

[Hook]
All you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing
War, you emcees, listen
What are you good for?
Absolutely nothing

Emcees don't you run away
Crash is coming out to play
Emcees don't you run away
Crash is coming out to play
Emcees don't you run away
Crash is coming out to play
Emcees don't you run away
Crash is coming out to play1Embed
